title: San Diego beats NAIA Warner 45-14
text:
San Diego beats NAIA Warner 45-14 By - Associated Press - 12:08 a.m., Sunday, October 25, 2015 
SAN DIEGO (AP) - Anthony Lawrence threw for 278 yards and four touchdowns on Saturday night, and San Diego scored the last 24 points to beat NAIA Warner 45-14. 
The Toreros (5-2) led 21-14 early in the second quarter when Lawrence led consecutive touchdown drives before the break. 
Jereke Armstrong added a third-quarter touchdown and Jack Flatau capped the scoring with a field goal early in the fourth. 
Armstrong finished with 71 yards and Blake Martin led San Diego on the ground with 88 yards and a score. Ross Dwelley had five catches for 75 yards and a touchdown. Justin Priest added five catches for 71 yards and a TD. 
Jeffrey Suarez Jr. had four receptions for 157 of Warner’s 195 yards through the air. He scored both of the Royals’ touchdowns including a 76-yarder in the first quarter.
